article.description: TUSCALOOSA, Ala. --  Jasmine James and Krista Donald each scored 18 points to help Georgia (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) beat Alabama 81-66 on Sunday.
article.headline: Jasmine James, Krista Donald lead No. 20 Georgia past Bama
article.linkText: James, Donald lead No. 20 Georgia past Bama
article.story:
TUSCALOOSA, Ala. --  Jasmine James and Krista Donald each scored 18 points to help Georgia (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) beat Alabama 81-66 on Sunday.

Leading by five at the half, Georgia (18-6, 7-4 SEC) scored two quick baskets to start the second half and the Lady Bulldogs never looked back.

Shafontaye Myers and Meghan Perkins scored 16 points each to led Alabama (10-14, 0-10).
